IRS990.Desc: THE OBJECTIVE OF THE UNION IS THE WELFARE AND MUTUAL PROTECTION OF ITS MEMBERS, TO REDUCE THE HOURS OF DAILY LABOR TO SECURE BETTER WORKING CONDITIONS AND ADEQUATE PAY FOR THEIR WORK AND CULTIVATE COMRADESHIP.

Form990PartVIISectionAGrp.TitleTxt: TRUSTEE - BEN PLAN - PAST / ORGANIZER - NEW

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE LOCAL MAINTAINS A PAC FUND WHICH WAS ESTABLISHED TO PROVIDE SUPPORT TO STATE AND LOCAL CANDIDATES FOR POLITICAL OFFICE WHOSE IDEALS ARE SIMILAR TO THOSE OF THE LOCAL AND ORGANIZED LABOR IN GENERAL.

OtherLiabilitiesOrgGrp.Desc: PAYROLL WITHHOLDING NOT REMITTED AT Y/E

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE LOCAL IS REQUIRED TO EVALUATE ITS TAX POSITION AND DISCLOSE THE AMOUNT OF A TAX LIABILITY IF THE LOCAL HAS TAKEN AN UNCERTAIN POSITION THAT MORE LIKELY THAN NOT WOULD NOT BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION BY TAX AUTHORITIES. THE LOCAL IS SUBJECT TO ROUTINE AUDITS BY TAXING JURISDICTIONS; HOWEVER, THERE ARE CURRENTLY NO AUDITS FOR ANY TAX PERIODS IN PROGRESS.

THE EXECUTIVE BOARD CAREFULLY REVIEWS ALL REQUESTS FOR DONATIONS AND GRANTS PRIOR TO THEIR APPROVAL AND DISBURSEMENT. APPROVAL IS GRANTED ONLY TO REPUTABLE ORGANIZATIONS AND INDIVIDUALS WHO HAVE SATISFIED THE BOARD'S DUE DILIGENCE. THE BOARD PERFORMS NO SUBSEQUENT MONITORING OF THE USE OF DONATIONS AND GRANTS. ALL RECORDS REGARDING DISBURSEMENT OF FUNDS ARE MAINTAINED AT THE LOCAL UNION OFFICE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE LOCAL'S GENERAL MEMBERSHIP IS COMPRISED OF INDIVIDUALS WHICH HAVE ANSWERED ALL QUESTIONS, TESTS AND WRITTEN EXAMINATIONS PROPOUNDED BY THE EXAMINATION COMMITTEE, PAID ALL APPLICABLE INITIATION FEES AND ANNUAL DUES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: JOURNEYMAN, 40-50-60 YEAR MEMBERS, APPRENTICES, AND NON BENEFICIAL MEMBERS ARE ELIGIBLE TO VOTE FOR OFFICERS OF THE LOCAL.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: CERTAIN EXECUTIVE BOARD DECISIONS ARE SUBJECT TO APPROVAL BY THE MEMBERSHIP.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 8B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE LOCAL DOES NOT HAVE A SEGREGATED COMMITTEE WHICH ACTS ON BEHALF OF THE GOVERNING BODY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 IS PREPARED BY AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTING FIRM AND PROVIDED TO THE ENTIRE EXECUTIVE BOARD FOR THEIR CAREFUL REVIEW AND APPROVAL. ONCE APPROVED, THE FORM IS SIGNED AND SUBMITTED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COMPENSATION OF OFFICERS AND BUSINESS AGENTS IS BASED UPON THE JOURNEYMAN'S RATE OF PAY AS DETAILED IN LOCAL'S BYLAWS BUT DETERMINED BY THE CURRENT COLLECTIVE BARGAINING AGREEMENT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
